@startuml
title Secure Video Recording System - General Sequence Diagram

actor User

participant "Video Source / Camera" as Camera
participant "YOLOv8 Engine" as YOLO
participant "Web Server" as Server
participant "Authentication Module" as Auth
participant "Crypto Module\n(AES-256-CBC + PBKDF2)" as Crypto
participant "Storage\n(.mp4.enc files)" as Storage
participant "Download Manager" as Download

== Recording Phase ==

loop Continuous Surveillance
    Camera -> YOLO : Video frames
    YOLO -> YOLO : Object detection
    YOLO -> YOLO : Detect human (confidence > 80%)

    alt Human detected
        YOLO -> YOLO : Start recording
        YOLO -> YOLO : Record video clip (30 sec)
        YOLO -> Server : Recorded video clip

        Server -> Crypto : Raw video data

        Crypto -> Crypto : Generate key using PBKDF2
        Crypto -> Crypto : Generate random IV
        Crypto -> Crypto : Encrypt using AES-256-CBC

        Crypto -> Storage : Save encrypted file (.mp4.enc)

    else No human detected
        YOLO -> YOLO : Continue monitoring
    end
end

== Playback Phase ==

User -> Server : Login request
Server -> Auth : Verify credentials
Auth --> Server : Authentication success
Server --> User : Session cookie

User -> Server : Request video list

Server -> Storage : Retrieve encrypted videos
Storage --> Server : List of .mp4.enc files

Server --> User : Display available videos

User -> Server : Select video
Server --> User : Request decryption password

User -> Server : Submit password

Server -> Storage : Retrieve encrypted file
Storage --> Server : Encrypted video data

Server -> Crypto : Send encrypted data + password

Crypto -> Crypto : Derive key (PBKDF2)
Crypto -> Crypto : Extract IV (first 16 bytes)
Crypto -> Crypto : AES-256-CBC decryption
Crypto -> Crypto : Remove PKCS7 padding

Crypto --> Server : Decrypted video stream

Server --> User : Stream video
User -> User : Watch video in HTML5 player

== Download Phase ==

User -> Server : Click "Download Video"

Server -> Storage : Retrieve encrypted file
Storage --> Server : Encrypted video

Server -> Crypto : Decrypt video using password

Crypto -> Crypto : Derive key (PBKDF2)
Crypto -> Crypto : Extract IV
Crypto -> Crypto : AES-256-CBC decryption

Crypto --> Server : Decrypted video file

Server -> Download : Send decrypted file
Download --> User : Download playable MP4 file

@enduml